President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 6-12, 2014 as National Volunteer Week. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of service and the role volunteers play in shaping a better nation. He acknowledges the countless acts of kindness and generosity carried out by Americans every day, and encourages citizens to commit to making service a part of their daily lives. The President also mentions various programs and initiatives, such as AmeriCorps and Senior Corps, that engage Americans in service. He emphasizes the resilience and unity of the American people in times of crisis, citing examples like the response to a mudslide in Washington State and a tornado in Oklahoma. President Obama urges individuals to visit Serve.gov to find service opportunities in their area.